<h1>Problem 962 - 2017 RMM, P1 of 6</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 6</h2>
<p>
<ul><li>Prove that every positive integer \(n\) can be written uniquely in the form 
\(n = \sum_{j=1}^{2k + 1} (-1)^{j - 1} 2^{m_j}\)
where \(k\geq 0\) and \(0\le m_1 < m_2 \cdots < m_{2k+1}\) are integers.</p>
<p>This number \(k\) is called <i>weight</i> of \(n\).</li><li>Find (in closed form) the difference between the number of positive integers at most \(2^{2017}\) with even weight and the number of positive integers at most \(2^{2017}\) with odd weight.</li></ul></p>
